  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The hypothesis of this study is that prolonged-storage RBCs are not inferior to short-storage
      RBCs for the time required to clear elevated blood lactate levels in children with severe
      anemia.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This study will measure the time to resolution of lactic acidosis in patients with severe
      anemia following blood transfusion.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
